{
  "text": "The mean perfusion-weighted image and the mean 0 image were used to estimate CBF using the single blood compartment model [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] : where \u0394 is the mean ASL difference signal between labeling and control images, 2 is the total inversion time equal to the sum of 1 and the postlabeling delay, 0 is the measured tissue proton density, and is the brain blood/tissue partition coefficient (assumed to be 0.9) [CITATION_4] .",
